    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Posable recreational toy or character dolls that are intended to be dressed in a variety of outfits reflecting contemporary or collector trends. Contemporary fashion dolls are usually made from plastic or vinyl, and are mass produced, though many variations exist. The current versions of this type of doll emerged in the mid-20th century and were based on a German doll called Bild Lilli, the design of which was acquired by American company Mattel, that then marketed it as Barbie. Many imitations and </Note_Text>
